Here are GUI examples for each language you mentioned, showing what kinds of frameworks or toolkits are commonly used:

üêç Python ‚Äì [Tkinter, PyQt, Kivy, wxPython]

Example: Tkinter

import tkinter as tk

root = tk.Tk()
root.title("Python GUI")
tk.Label(root, text="Hello from Python!").pack()
tk.Button(root, text="Click Me", command=lambda: print("Clicked!")).pack()
root.mainloop()


üêò PHP ‚Äì [Web-based GUI (HTML/CSS/JS + PHP backend)]

Example: Basic HTML form + PHP handling

<!-- index.php -->
<form method="post">
  <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Enter name" />
  <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
</form>

<?php
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    echo "Hello, " . htmlspecialchars($_POST["name"]);
}
?>


üêò PHP doesn't do desktop GUI natively ‚Äì it's usually paired with HTML for web UIs.

üìä MATLAB ‚Äì [App Designer, GUIDE (deprecated)]

Example: Simple UI Button

function simpleGUI
    f = figure('Name', 'MATLAB GUI');
    uicontrol('Style', 'pushbutton', 'String', 'Click Me',...
        'Position', [100 100 100 50],...
        'Callback', @(src, event) disp('Button clicked!'));
end


‚òï Java ‚Äì [Swing, JavaFX]

Example: Java Swing GUI

import javax.swing.*;

public class HelloWorldGUI {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        JFrame frame = new JFrame("Java GUI");
        JButton button = new JButton("Click Me");
        button.addActionListener(e -> System.out.println("Button clicked!"));
        frame.add(button);
        frame.setSize(200, 100);
        frame.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        frame.setVisible(true);
    }
}


üß± C# ‚Äì [WinForms, WPF, MAUI, Avalonia]

Example: WinForms

System;
using System.Windows.Forms;

public class HelloWorld : Form {
    public HelloWorld() {
        Button btn = new Button { Text = "Click Me" };
        btn.Click += (sender, e) => MessageBox.Show("Hello!");
        Controls.Add(btn);
    }

    [STAThread]
    static void Main() {
        Application.Run(new HelloWorld());
    }
}


üí£ C++ ‚Äì [Qt, wxWidgets, MFC, ImGui]

Example: Qt

#include <QApplication>
#include <QPushButton>

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    QApplication app(argc, argv);
    QPushButton button("Click Me");
    button.show();
    return app.exec();
}
